Bus-sized fatberg weighing 40 tonnes cleared from London sewer
https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2019/oct/29/bus-sized-fatberg-cleared-from-london-sewer

Blockage in Greenwich prompts Thames Water to reissue warning about waste disposal
格林威治的阻塞物促使泰唔士河水利局重新發布廢棄物處理警告

A 40-tonne fatberg the size of a double-decker bus has been cleared from a London sewer by Thames Water engineers who pulled out some of it by hand.
一個雙層巴士高重達 40 噸的脂肪硬塊從倫敦下水道被泰唔士河水利局曾經徒手清出一部分的工程師清了出來。

The mass of fat, grease and other materials that weighed the same as three red buses,
was discovered earlier this year clogging up a sewer in Greenwich, the water company said.
水公司表示，這一坨由脂肪、油狀物、和其他材料組成稱起來相當於三台紅色巴士總重的噁爛巨無霸今年初被發現堵住了格林威治下水道。
註：為什麼是紅色巴士呢？這跟台灣計程車是黃色的是一樣的道理。截至 2021 年，倫敦有 675 條巴士路線，由 9,000 多輛巴士提供服務，自推出以來的幾十年裡，紅色倫敦巴士已成為這座城市的象徵。

It took three weeks for Thames Water workers to clear the “disgusting” blockage which at points took up 80% of the sewer’s capacity.
泰晤士河水利局的工作人員花了三週來清理這一團位於負責高達該下水道 80% 容量地點的"令人作嘔"的阻塞物。

They used a combination of high-powered water jets to blast it loose and removed debris by hand.
他們使用了高壓水槍套組來沖散它並用手移除碎塊。

// Thames Water: 是英國水利機構，詳見網站 https://www.thameswater.co.uk/

// fatberg: noun [ C ] UK（下水道中的）肥球，油脂硬塊

// Thames: 泰唔士河

// reissue: verb [ T ], 重印；重新發行；再版
The recording has been reissued to celebrate the conductor's 80th birthday.
為了慶祝這位指揮家的80壽辰，重新發行了這張唱片。

// disposal: noun [ U ], 清除；處理；拋棄
waste disposal
廢物處理

// tonne: noun [ C ] 英國人比較愛用，公噸。
Oil deliveries will fall 2.5 million tonnes short this year.
今年的石油輸送量將下降250萬公噸。

// double-decker: noun [ C ], 雙層
double-decker bed
雙層床
double-decker maisonette
雙層小別墅

// sewer: noun [ C ] 下水道；排水管；陰溝
A complicated system of sewers runs under the city.
城市的地底下布有複雜的排水系統。

// pull out: 拉出

// grease: noun [ U ] 油，油脂；油膩狀物
The dinner plates were thick with grease.
餐盤上厚厚一層油。

// clog: verb [ I or T ] （使）阻塞，（使）堵塞；塞上
Eating too much fat causes your arteries to clog (up).
攝入過多脂肪會導致動脈栓塞。

// disgusting: adjective 令人厭惡的，讓人憎惡的，使人反感的
Passengers were kept for three hours in a disgusting waiting room.
乘客被迫在令人厭惡的候車室裡等了好幾個小時。

// blockage: noun [ C or U ] 障礙物；堵塞，阻礙
His death was caused by a blockage in one of his arteries.
他死於動脈阻塞。

// capacity: noun 容積，容量
The stadium has a seating capacity of 50,000.
這個體育場能容納五萬人。

// water jet: 噴水槍

// blast: verb 原意是炸毀；爆破 ，但是高能水槍不是爆破用的，所以這裡應該是沖刷
A tunnel was to be blasted through the mountains.
要在群山中開鑿一條隧道

// loose: adjective 鬆的，鬆動的
The nails in the wall had worked themselves loose.
橋上的釘子已經鬆動了。

// debris: noun [ U ] 碎片，殘駭
Debris from the aircraft was scattered over a large area.
飛機殘駭散落在一片很大的區域。


Fatbergs are formed when fat, oil and grease are poured down sinks and drains and combine with items that should not be flushed down the toilet, such as unflushable wet wipes, nappies and cotton buds.
脂肪凝塊是由倒入水槽的脂肪、油、油狀物被排出（到下水道）後和不應該沖入馬桶的物品（例如不能沖入馬桶的溼紙巾、尿布、和棉籤）所結合而成。

*tip: 來解釋一下這一句的讀法。
句子主體： S + be 動詞 + pp. 是個被動式。
Fatbergs are formed (...) 其實括號裡面的都是描述 fatberg 怎麼形成的。是附加的說明。

fat, oil and grease are poured down sinks and drains and combine with items (...) 括號中的又是說明。
xxx are poured
	and drains
	and combine with items ....
xxx 是主詞，後面用 and 連接了三個動詞

items that should not be flushed down the toilet, such as (什麼東西)
items 是主詞，that 後面是形容詞子句，用來告訴我們 items 是什麼。

// pour: verb 倒，注，灌
I spilled the juice while I was pouring it.
我倒果汁時不小心弄灑了。

// sink: noun [ C ] （廚房的）水槽，洗碗槽；（浴室的）洗臉盆
a bathroom/kitchen sink
浴室／廚房水槽

// drain: verb （使）排出，（使）排放，放乾（液體）
We drained the pond and filled it with fresh water.
我們把池塘中的水放乾後重新注入清水。

// flush: verb (TOILET) 沖洗（抽水馬桶）
My children never flush the toilet after them.
我的孩子們用過馬桶後從來不沖。

// unflushable: adj. 不能沖入馬桶的

// wipe: noun [ C ] （濕）抹布；（濕）紙巾；（濕）手巾
baby wipes
嬰兒紙巾

// nappy: noun [ C ] UK 尿布
I knew William when he was still in nappies (= when he was a baby).
威廉還穿尿布的時候，我就認識他了。

// cotton bud: noun [ C ] UK （尤指用於清潔耳朵的）棉棒


Thames Water’s network protection team has been visiting food establishments in the area,
to make sure they are not putting fat, grease and oil down their sinks and that fat traps are installed and working.
泰唔士河水利局的保護網路團隊已經拜訪了該區域的食品企業，確保他們沒有把脂肪、油污、和油倒入他們的水槽，並且確保他們確實有安裝攔油器並且有發揮作用。

Matt Rimmer, Thames Water’s head of waste networks,
said: “This was a massive and disgusting blockage that took a great deal of effort and teamwork to clear and get the sewer working well again.
泰唔士河水利局的保護網路團隊的領導者 Matt Rimmer 表示，這是一個需要花費大量努力和團隊合作才能清除並再次恢復下水道功能的巨大噁爛阻塞物。

// establishment: noun 企業；機構；單位
an educational/financial/religious establishment
教育／金融／宗教機構

// trap: noun 陷阱；夾子；捕捉器
The fox got its foot caught in a trap.
狐狸的一隻腳被夾子夾住了。


“I’m happy that our team was able to get down and work hard to quickly to clear the fatberg before it could cause problems for our customers and the environment.
我很開心我們的團隊可以下去並且勤奮快速地在這個脂肪阻塞物對我們的消費者和環境造成問題之前清除它。

“We’d urge everyone to help fight the fatberg by only flushing the 3Ps – pee, poo and paper – as well as disposing of fat and oils in the bin, not the sink.”
我們會敦促所有人採取只沖 3P (進馬桶) - 尿、糞、衛生紙 - 以及在垃圾桶處理脂肪和油汙而非在水槽的方式來協助對抗脂肪阻塞物。

// urge: verb [ I or T ] 敦促；驅策；力勸
[ + to infinitive ] Lawyers will urge the parents to take further legal action.
律師們會力勸家長們採取進一步的法律行動。

// pee: noun 尿

// poo: noun [ C or U ] UK informal 屎，大便
Ugh, it looks like poo!
啊，它看上去像大便！

// dispose of sb/sth: phrasal verb with dispose verb 清除；處理；解決；擊敗
It took only five minutes for the world champion to dispose of (= defeat) his opponent.
世界冠軍只用五分鐘就擊敗了對手。

// bin: noun [ C ] 垃圾箱
recycling bins for old newspapers, bottles, and cans
回收舊報紙、舊瓶子和舊罐頭盒的廢物箱。


