嗨，伙計，什麼事？

// billionaire: noun [ C ] 億萬富翁，擁有十億家產的人


Speaking with Vanity Fair, the musician recalled how they had once found a hole in her side of the mattress while living in Los Angeles.
在接受浮華世界採訪時，這位音樂家回憶起當他住在洛杉磯時，他們發現她睡的那一側的床墊上有個洞。

Instead of buying a new one, she said, Musk suggested that they bring over the mattress from her home instead.
她說，與其買一張新的床墊， Musk 建議(他們)從她家裡搬舊的來用。

"Like, bro wouldn't even get a new mattress," she told the publication.
"就好像歐巴甚至不會買新床墊，"她告訴浮華世界雜誌。

"Bro does not live like a billionaire. Bro lives at times below the poverty line," Grimes said, per Vanity Fair.
Grimes 對浮華雜誌說，"歐巴活的不像是個億萬富翁。歐巴有時候（生活水平像是）活在（聯合國定義的）貧窮門檻以下。"

