Changing Times
https://www.timeforkids.com/g2/changing-times-3/?rl=en-500

The Colosseum is an ancient stadium in Rome, Italy.
古羅馬圓形大競技場是義大利首都羅馬古代的競技場。

Today, people from around the world visit the ruins of the Colosseum.
今日，人們從世界各地來拜訪古羅馬圓形大競技場的遺跡。

The drawing on the right shows the stadium as it looked long ago.
右邊的圖片顯示了很久以前競技場的樣子。

Rome is an ancient city in Italy. For more than 500 years, it was the center of a great empire.
羅馬是義大利的古城。在五百年以前，它曾經是偉大帝國的中心。

The city’s wealth and power can be seen in monuments that are still standing.
我們仍然可以從依舊矗立的遺跡看出它過往的富有和繁盛。

One of the grandest is the Colosseum.
這其中最偉大的就是古羅馬圓形大競技場。

This stadium was built about 2,000 years ago. It held 50,000 people.
這個競技場是 2000 年以前建造的，可以容納 50000 名觀眾。

Romans went there to watch battles between trained fighters, called gladiators.
羅馬人去哪裡觀賞訓練精良的戰士的打鬥。這些戰士又被稱為 gladiators 。

These warriors wore armor and fought with swords. They were heroes to their fans.
這些戰士穿著盔甲並且使用劍戰鬥。對粉絲來說，這些人就是他們的英雄。

Beneath the arena were passages.
在競技場的下方是通路。

Wild animals were kept there. Sometimes, a lion, wolf, or bear was brought into the arena.
野生動物被飼養在這裡。有時候獅子、野狼、或是熊會被帶到競技場。

Could a gladiator survive a fight with the ferocious beast?
gladiator 是否能從與這些猛獸的搏鬥中生還呢？

The crowd would cheer as their hero fought a bloody battle.
當他們的英雄奮勇血戰的時候，群眾們為之歡呼。

// Colosseum: n. 古羅馬圓形大競技場

// ancient: adj. 古代的
We were impressed by the ruins of an ancient building.
我們對一處古建築廢墟印象頗深。

// stadium: n [ C ] 體育場，運動場；球場；競技場
The stadium was filled for the final baseball game.
體育場被觀看最後一場棒球比賽的人群擠滿了。

// Rome: n. 羅馬（義大利首都）

// drawing: n. [C] 圖畫；圖形
He made a drawing of flowers and plants.
他畫了一張花卉畫。

// ruin: n. 廢墟；遺跡[P]
We visited the ruins of the temple.
我們參觀了那個廟宇的遺跡。

// monument: n.[C] 歷史遺跡，遺址
The ruins of the castle are an ancient monument, which the government pays money to preserve.
這一城堡廢墟是古代的遺跡，政府出錢加以保存。

// grand: a. 雄偉的；堂皇的；盛大的
He lives in a grand house.
他住在一棟富麗堂皇的房子裡。

// gladiator n. 【史】鬥劍者，鬥士

// armor: n.[U] 盔甲
The knight was completely clad in armor.
那位騎士全身披掛盔甲。

// beneath: prep. 在……之下；向……下面
The sun is now beneath the horizon.
太陽此刻落到地平線下了。

// arena: n.[C] 古羅馬圓形劇場中央的）角鬥場，競技場
an arena for boxing matches
拳擊比賽場

// passages: passage 的名詞複數 通路；水路；出入口[C]
Magellan was trying to find a passage to the Indian Ocean.
麥哲倫試圖找到一條通向印度洋的通道。

// ferocious: a. 兇猛的；殘忍的
a ferocious attack
一場兇猛的進攻

// crowd: n. 大眾[the S]
You can do what you want to do, but never follow the crowd.
你想做什麼就做什麼，可別隨波逐流。


The Stadio Olimpico is where Romans go to watch the city’s soccer teams compete.
羅馬奧林匹克體育場是羅馬人欣賞成足球競賽的地方。

The stadium has also hosted World Cup games and the Olympics.
這個競技場還舉辦過世界杯足球賽和奧運。

Sports are still important to Romans. But today, their favorite game is soccer.
運動對羅馬人來說仍然很重要。但是時至今日，他們最喜歡的賽事是足球。

In Rome, soccer is known as football. The game is played in the Stadio Olimpico.
在羅馬， soccer 又叫做 football。賽事在羅馬奧林匹克體育場舉辦。

The arena can hold 74,000 people.
競技場可以容納 74000 人。

Rome has two teams.
羅馬有兩個隊伍。

They are fierce rivals.
他們是競爭激烈的對手。

Players charge up and down the field.
選手們在場上衝來衝去。

They shoot for a goal.
他們射門是為了得分。

There’s action off the field, too.
就算下了場也有活動。

Fans wave flags and sing songs.
粉絲揮動旗幟並且唱歌。

When a goal is scored, the stadium erupts in cheers.
當進球得分， 競技場就爆出了歡呼聲。

Soccer games take place on Sundays.
足球賽通常在禮拜天舉行。

But for Romans, soccer is a part of everyday life.
但是對羅馬人來說，足球是每日生活的一部分。

All week long, fans talk and argue about soccer.
整個禮拜粉絲們都在談並爭議關於足球賽的事。

They are loyal to their teams.
他們對支持的隊伍非常忠誠。

To them, soccer players are heroes.
對他們來說，足球運動員就是他們的英雄。

// Stadio Olimpico: 羅馬奧林匹克體育場

// compete: verb [ I ] 競爭
It's difficult for a small shop to compete against/with the big supermarkets.
小超市很難與大超市競爭

// fierce: adjective 猛烈的；激烈的；駭人的
a fierce attack/battle
猛烈的進攻／激烈的戰鬥

// rival: noun [ C ] 競爭對手；敵手
He beat his closest/nearest rival by 20 marks.
他以領先20分的成績打敗了和他水平最接近的對手。

// charge: verb  [ I or T ] 猛衝；向…衝去
The bull lowered its horns and charged.
公牛俯下牛角發動進攻。

// up and down: 起起伏伏地，上上下下地
My little girl started jumping up and down with rage when she heard she couldn't go.
我的小女兒在得知她不能去後非常生氣，開始不停地跳上跳下。

// erupt: verb [ I ] 爆發（感情）；激烈地表達（感情）
The crowd erupted in applause and cheering.
人群中爆發出掌聲和歡呼聲。

// loyal: adjective 忠實的，忠誠的
Jack has been a loyal worker in this company for almost 50 years.
傑克是這間公司忠誠的員工，已經工作了快50年了。


